    Customize the Result Screen. Shown for server-side work and response handling.

      • customActivityIndicatorAnimation

        public int customActivityIndicatorAnimation
        Configure an SVG element to display on the Result Screen for the activity indicator animation during server-side work. Only available for API >= 21.
        Note: All resources required for the vector drawable animation needs to be included in your app's res directory before launching.
        Note: The activity indicator animation is displayed indefinitely during the server-side work, so the custom animation should be set to loop/repeat infinitely. If the animation ends before the activity indicator is dismissed, the animation will be restarted.
        If this is set to an animated vector drawable, the drawable supplied will be used instead of the default activity indicator animation or any rotating-image animation configured with FaceTecResultScreenCustomization.customActivityIndicatorImage.
        If this is 0, FaceTecResultScreenCustomization.customActivityIndicatorImage will be used. If FaceTecResultScreenCustomization.customActivityIndicatorImage is 0, the default activity indicator animation will be used.
        Default is 0.

      • resultAnimationSuccessBackgroundImage

        @DrawableRes
public int resultAnimationSuccessBackgroundImage
        Image displayed behind the result foreground animation for success scenarios.
        If image is configured, default result background animation will be hidden.
        Default is set to 0 and will fallback to using the default result background animation, which respects the color assigned to .resultAnimationBackgroundColor.

      • resultAnimationUnsuccessBackgroundImage

        @DrawableRes
public int resultAnimationUnsuccessBackgroundImage
        Image displayed behind the result foreground animation for unsuccess scenarios. Unsuccess result animations are only shown for unsuccessful Photo ID Match attempts.
        If image is configured, default result background animation will be hidden.
        Default is set to 0 and will fallback to using the default result background animation, which respects the color assigned to .resultAnimationBackgroundColor.

      • customResultAnimationSuccess

        @DrawableRes
public int customResultAnimationSuccess
        Configure an animated vector drawable to display on the Result Screen for success scenarios. Only available for API >= 21.
        Note: All resources required for the vector drawable animation needs to be included in your app's res directory before launching.
        Note: The result animation is displayed for 2 seconds, so custom animation timing should be configured accordingly.
        If this is set to an animated vector drawable resource id, the drawable supplied will be used instead of the default success animation or any success image configured with FaceTecResultScreenCustomization.resultAnimationSuccessBackgroundImage.
        If this is 0, the default success animation will be used.
        Default is 0.

      • customResultAnimationUnsuccess

        @DrawableRes
public int customResultAnimationUnsuccess
        Configure an animated vector drawable to display on the Result Screen for unsuccess scenarios. Unsuccess result animations are only shown for unsuccessful Photo ID Match attempts. Only available for API >= 21.
        Note: All resources required for the vector drawable animation needs to be included in your app's res directory before launching.
        Note: The result animation is displayed for 2 seconds, so custom animation timing should be configured accordingly.
        If this is set to an animated vector drawable resource id, the drawable supplied will be used instead of the default unsuccess animation or any unsuccess image configured with FaceTecResultScreenCustomization.resultAnimationUnsuccessBackgroundImage.
        If this is 0, the default unsuccess animation will be used.
        Default is 0.

      • customStaticResultAnimationSuccess

        @DrawableRes
public int customStaticResultAnimationSuccess
        Configure a static vector drawable to display on the Result Screen for success scenarios. Only available for API < 21.
        Note: All resources required for the vector drawable needs to be included in your app's res directory before launching.
        If this is set to a vector drawable resource id, the drawable supplied will be used instead of the default static success animation or any success image configured with FaceTecResultScreenCustomization.resultAnimationSuccessBackgroundImage.
        If this is 0, the default success animation will be used.
        Default is 0.

      • customStaticResultAnimationUnsuccess

        @DrawableRes
public int customStaticResultAnimationUnsuccess
        Configure a static vector drawable to display on the Result Screen for unsuccess scenarios. Unsuccess result animations are only shown for unsuccessful Photo ID Match attempts. Only available for API < 21.
        Note: All resources required for the vector drawable needs to be included in your app's res directory before launching.
        If this is set to a vector drawable resource id, the drawable supplied will be used instead of the default static unsuccess animation or any unsuccess image configured with FaceTecResultScreenCustomization.resultAnimationUnsuccessBackgroundImage.
        If this is 0, the default unsuccess animation will be used.
        Default is 0.
